wiki.summary: "Sweetest Pie" is the lead single from Megan Thee Stallion's second studio album, Traumazine. It features English singer Dua Lipa. The track takes the shape of a catchy, upbeat and sultry pop song, with both Megan and Dua radiating confidence and owning their sexuality via their lyrics —which also make use of dessert euphemisms. The music video juxtaposes beautiful things with horrific things, which is apt given the overall sweet but dangerous theme. Read more on Last.fm.
